- "Garden" refers to the game session;
- "Flowers" refer to the features;
- "Gardeners" refer to the users;
- "Tended" refers to the usage of the features.

- 'top 3 most used features' refers to the features with the highest usage counts within each session;
- 'session' refers to a specific game session identified by `session_id`;
- 'feature' refers to a gameplay element identified by `feature_id`.

- 'Recent sessions' refers to sessions created after January 1, 2022;
- 'Popular' is determined by the count of distinct sessions in which the feature was used;
- 'General' features are a specific type of feature in the database;
- 'Testers' are users with the role 'tester'.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.type) AS feature_count
FROM features AS T2
INNER JOIN prerequisites AS T3 ON T2.feature_id = T3.feature_id;

